  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with atrial fibrillation are often anticoagulated with Warfarin. Warfarin has a
      narrow therapeutic window requiring frequent monitoring. This study aims to investigate the
      incidence of adverse events in the &quot;real world&quot; for patients receiving Warfarin for lone
      atrial fibrillation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
